Style Recalc Impact of Speculation Rules

The unordered list at the bottom bears the CSS class .demo-list. This CSS class is not used in any <style> block or external stylesheet. The only place it is used is within speculation rules as seen here:

In spite of that the selector still impacts style recalc performance. if you do a performance capture of the page with "Enable CSS selector stats (slow)" turned on, and then click the button you will find the selector .demo-list a listed as one of many "100% slow-path" offenders, although it should not be part of the style recalc process.
